This project was carried out during the “Embedded Systems” hands-on course to design an electronic circuit and programming an ARM microcontroller to control a temperature chamber. The following topics have been covered during this course:ARM Microcontrollers ArchitectureDesign Circuits for Power Supply - Linear/Switching RegulatorsDesign Circuits for Digital InputOutputDesign Circuits for Analog Input/Output - Protection CircuitKeypad and LCD InterfacingRS485 Communication InterfaceSTM32 Programming - GPIO, DMA, ADC, USART, InterruptsLCD and Keypad Interface ProgrammingHMI Communication - Modbus ProtocolScreenshots&lt;! &mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&ndash;Slideshow&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&ndash; &gt;
